## Important Notes

- Use the config_id mapping from `validate-sweep-trace.mdc` to pair model and sweep configs. Only analyze matched pairs.
- The `arguments` comparison must be done on **raw** values (not normalized). This is the opposite of `validate-sweep-trace.mdc` which strips ignored keys.
- `memory_config.hash` is almost always different and is the most common reason for hash mismatch. If this is the ONLY difference, note that the configs are functionally identical and the mismatch is expected until the tracer is updated.
- When multiple categories apply to a single pair, list all of them.
- `json.dumps(obj, sort_keys=True)` is deterministic for the same Python object, so any byte-level difference in the serialized form means the input objects differ structurally.
